  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: eef041081aed1064791c1fe85b5ec65e, type: 3}
  m_Name: SHMode
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  Title: Lighting data mode
  Body: '<b>L1</b>


    Full RGB light colour as well as individual X, Y, and Z
    direction components for each colour channel for a total of 12 channels per each
    voxel.


    Most lifelike, and will capture multicolour light shining on the
    same spot in different directions, but will also generate the largest file size.


    -


    <b>MonoL1</b>


    Full
    RGB light colour, but unlike full L1, uses just a single set of X, Y, and Z components
    rather than a set per colour channel for 6 total channels per voxel.


    Isn''t
    able to represent different colours shining from different directions on one
    voxel as accurately, but baked texture size is ~33% smaller versus full L1 at
    16bpc, or ~50% smaller at 8bpc since the unused alpha channel can be dropped
    entirely. Good enough for the majority of scenarios.


    -


    <b>MonoL0</b>


    Monochromatic
    light intensity and X, Y, and Z direction components for 4 channels per voxel.


    Losing
    the ability to vary colour across a single snapshot makes this the smallest baking
    format available, ~67% smaller than full L1.

'
  Images: []
